quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  4,128,"And if a woman fears from her husband contempt or evasion, there is no sin upon them if they make terms of settlement between them - and settlement is best. And present in [human] souls is stinginess.[1] But if you do good and fear Allāh - then indeed Allāh is ever, of what you do, Aware.","[1] i.e., holding on to self-interests."
  4,129,"And you will never be able to be equal [in feeling] between wives, even if you should strive [to do so]. So do not incline completely [toward one] and leave another hanging.[1] And if you amend [your affairs] and fear Allāh - then indeed, Allāh is ever Forgiving and Merciful.","[1] Neither divorced nor enjoying the rights of marriage."
  4,130,"But if they separate [by divorce], Allāh will enrich each [of them] from His abundance. And ever is Allāh Encompassing and Wise.",""
  4,131,"And to Allāh belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And We have instructed those who were given the Scripture before you and yourselves to fear Allāh. But if you disbelieve - then to Allāh belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And ever is Allāh Free of need and Praiseworthy.",""
  4,132,"And to Allāh belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And sufficient is Allāh as Disposer of affairs.[1]","[1] Refer to footnote in 3:173."
  4,133,"If He wills, He can do away with you, O people, and bring others [in your place]. And ever is Allāh competent to do that.",""
  4,134,"Whoever desires the reward of this world - then with Allāh is the reward of this world and the Hereafter. And ever is Allāh Hearing and Seeing.",""
